8:
All the rumors are about him lately.
It seems that he fights like a beast,
shrugging off fatal hits with ease.
12: You sure those aren't about you?
16:
It can't be, because the person in
question wears a helmet.
21:
It's possible he is like me. He
apparently lives in a village to the
east. I intend to see him.
25:
Hmm... It's weird that these rumors
are so detailed, don't you think?
30:
That village itself is also very
suspicious.
37:
More like the opposite: it's so devoid
of action that it's weird.
40:
Most small settlements without a
name tend to be hotspots for bandit
activities.
43:
But I've heard nothing about attacks
in that area. Really makes my Lilie
senses tingle.
47:
Something definitely smells off
about this...
52:
This opportunity might give me a
clue about my creator. I don't care if
it's a trap.
56:
Londahl, why do you want to meet
your creator?
60: ...I want to find out why he made me.
65:
*sigh* Guess there's no getting
around it. You're going no matter
what, right? We'll come with.
76:
This place is shabbier than I
pictured. But why's it so quiet?
79:
There's not a single sign of life, as if
the town is abandoned...
84: You must be the rumored man.
95:
Relax, I only knocked him out. Which
was pretty damn nice of me,
considering he came at us without
even saying hello.
100: As I thought, he is the same as me
105: Oh, you've gotta be kidding me...
114:
This isn't good. They won't last long
at this rate... Nimbus, Alk, Light...
116:
So you're the armor I've heard so
much about. You came, just as I
knew you would.
121:
As much as I wish I could claim
credit, I'm afraid not. But I am like
you, in that I wish to meet the Grand
Creator.
125:
Yes, the one who taught me of the
cryptic artifacts... The genius who
wielded knowledge of arts unknown
to the common man.
126:
Yet he disappeared one day, before
he could teach me everything he
knew!
128:
The true nature of magic and
curses... The very secrets of the
world... He should have given them
all to me!
130:
...So the helmets must be based off
my design. Did you spread those
rumors to lure me here?
132:
A necessary step in my plan to meet
him once again. You'll help me from
now on, won't you?
137:
Those helmets lacked minds of their
own, so you must be controlling
them. If I defeat you, I'll defeat them.
139:
I can get information out of you
once I save my allies.
142:
Hahaha... You were correct to
assume the helmets were based off
you. But that means I can control
you as well!
148:
No matter how sentient you may be,
a fabricated will can never
150:
Ahhh... Impossible, m-my magic is
superior...
159:
Sheeesh, I thought we were done
for! Seriously, I was a hair away from
losing my head when all those
people fell over!
163:
Guess everything worked out in the
end though. We managed to
capture that crazy crook.
168:
That's true, buuut... The Guild Knights
haven't gotten any useful
information out of him.
172:
Good grief. We're coming out of this
empty-handed, then.
177:
About that... It's all right if we forget
about finding my creator for now.
182: Uh, didja hit your head or something?
186:
No. I never had a head in the first
place.
190:
I would rather prioritize finding a
way to return Lloyd to normal.
192: Do you think... that desire is strange?
201:
That doesn't change your original
goal much, does it? Your creator
made you. He'd know best how to fix
him.
205:
Nimbus makes a good point. We'll
be with you the whole way through,
Londahl.
213: Ah, Lloyd... Did you smile just now?
